The paper deals with the problem of maintaining a minimum spanning tree (MST) in a dynamic graph that is being processed by a cluster of computers. This problem is related to distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.DM), parallel and distributed computing (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on distributed algorithms for processing graph updates, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.LG.
